Britons who feel they are living in a state of permanent crisis received some relief last week with the start of a nationwide vaccination campaign against the coronavirus pandemic.
This nine-month-long purgatory has killed more than 61,000 people in the UK, devastated the economy and disrupted many thousands of lives in an unprecedented way.



