* * *
A pipe burst in a doctor’s house, so he called a plumber. The plumber unpacked his tools, fiddled around for 10 minutes, then handed the doctor a bill for £300. “This is outrageous,” said the doctor. “I don’t even make that much as a doctor.” Replied the plumber, “Neither did I when I was a doctor.”
* * *
A Hindu, a rabbi and a lawyer were driving through the rural areas when their car broke down. A nearby farmer said they could stay the night but he had only two spare beds, so one person must use the barn.
The Hindu agreed, but returned to the house moments later saying there was a cow in the barn and since cows were sacred, he could not possibly sleep there. The rabbi took his place but he fled, too, because there was a pig there and pigs were anathema to Jews. Finally, the lawyer said he would go.
Moments later there was a knock on the farmhouse door. It was the cow and the pig.



